---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'April 16, 2025';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — Brewio"
  description="How Brewio collects, uses, and protects your personal information."
>
  <Nav />

  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="page-header-inner">
      <div class="page-eyebrow">Legal</div>
      <h1 class="page-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="page-meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <main class="content">
    <div class="content-inner">

      <p class="lead">
        Brewio ("we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy.
        This policy explains what information we collect when you use the Brewio mobile
        application, how we use it, and the choices you have.
      </p>

      <section>
        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

        <h3>Account Information</h3>
        <p>
          When you sign in with Apple or Google, we receive your name and email address
          from the authentication provider. We store this to identify your account and
          personalise your experience.
        </p>

        <h3>Content You Create</h3>
        <p>We store the data you enter in the app, including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Brew logs — method, dose, grind size, tasting notes, ratings</li>
          <li>Bean stash entries — name, roaster, roast date, weight</li>
          <li>Custom recipes you create</li>
          <li>Profile preferences and settings</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Usage Data</h3>
        <p>
          We may collect anonymised usage data (e.g. which features are used most often)
          to improve the app. This data cannot be used to identify you personally.
        </p>

        <h3>Purchase Information</h3>
        <p>
          If you subscribe to Brewio Premium, purchases are processed through Apple App
          Store or Google Play. We use RevenueCat to manage subscription status. We never
          store your payment card details — these are handled entirely by Apple or Google.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>To provide and sync your coffee journal across devices</li>
          <li>To manage your account and subscription status</li>
          <li>To calculate and display your brewing stats, streaks, and badges</li>
          <li>To improve app features and fix bugs</li>
          <li>To respond to support requests you send us</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do not sell your data to third parties. Ever.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>Brewio uses the following third-party services, each with their own privacy policies:</p>

        <div class="service-table">
          <div class="service-row service-row-header">
            <span>Service</span>
            <span>Purpose</span>
          </div>
          <div class="service-row">
            <span><strong>Supabase</strong></span>
            <span>Database and backend infrastructure</span>
          </div>
          <div class="service-row">
            <span><strong>Apple Sign In</strong></span>
            <span>Authentication</span>
          </div>
          <div class="service-row">
            <span><strong>Google Sign In</strong></span>
            <span>Authentication</span>
          </div>
          <div class="service-row">
            <span><strong>RevenueCat</strong></span>
            <span>Subscription management</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. Data Storage & Security</h2>
        <p>
          Your data is stored securely on Supabase infrastructure hosted in the European
          Union. We use industry-standard encryption in transit (TLS) and at rest.
          Access to production data is strictly limited to essential personnel only.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          We retain your data for as long as your account is active. If you delete your
          account, we will delete your personal data within 30 days, except where we are
          required to retain it by law.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>Depending on your location, you may have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Access the personal data we hold about you</li>
          <li>Correct inaccurate data</li>
          <li>Request deletion of your data ("right to be forgotten")</li>
          <li>Export your data in a portable format</li>
          <li>Object to or restrict certain processing</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise any of these rights, contact us at
          <a href="mailto:hello@brewio.app">hello@brewio.app</a>.
          We will respond within 30 days.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Brewio is not directed at children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly
          collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided
          us with personal data, please contact us and we will delete it promptly.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will update
          the "last updated" date at the top. For significant changes, we will notify you
          through the app or by email.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us:</p>
        <div class="contact-block">
          <p><strong>Brewio</strong></p>
          <p>Email: <a href="mailto:hello@brewio.app">hello@brewio.app</a></p>
          <p>Website: <a href="https://brewio.app">brewio.app</a></p>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  /* ── Page header ── */
  .page-header {
    background: var(--dark);
    padding: 8rem 2rem 4rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-dark);
  }

  .page-header-inner {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .page-eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--amber);
    margin-bottom: 0.875rem;
  }

  .page-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 4vw, 3.5rem);
    color: var(--cream);
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .page-meta {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: rgba(250,247,242,0.4);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }

  /* ── Content ── */
  .content {
    background: var(--cream);
    padding: 5rem 2rem 7rem;
  }

  .content-inner {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--text-dark);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--text-dark);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-dark);
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 0.875rem;
  }

  ul {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.875rem 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  li {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--amber);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  a:hover { color: var(--amber-light); }

  /* Service table */
  .service-table {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .service-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    gap: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .service-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .service-row-header {
    background: white;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--text-light);
  }

  /* Contact block */
  .contact-block {
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  .contact-block p { margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
  .contact-block p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .page-header { padding: 6rem 1.25rem 2.5rem; }
    .content { padding: 3rem 1.25rem 5rem; }

    .service-row {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 0.2rem;
    }

    .service-row-header { display: none; }
  }
</style>
